    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_14_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_14",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S is a superlative example of the 996.2 chassis, maintained to a concours standard. Power is delivered by the M96/03 3.6L flat-six, featuring a documented IMS bearing upgrade and a flawless bore-scope report. The Getrag G96/31 six-speed manual transmission offers crisp, tactile engagement, feeding a sophisticated all-wheel-drive system with a viscous center coupling. The suspension geometry remains factory-spec, utilizing Bilstein dampers and uprated anti-roll bars for neutral cornering. Braking performance is anchored by four-piston monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing zero heat checking. This vehicle presents with impeccable paint depth and a perfectly synchronized valvetrain, representing the pinnacle of the wide-body 996 aesthetic and performance.",
